<h2 id="visual-studio-code">Visual Studio Code</h2>

<p><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/">Visual Studio Code</a> is my favorite text editor for heavier tasks than writing simple code. Below is a list of the extensions and the theme I use.</p>

<p><img src="/images/compsci-images/vscode-1.png" alt="" /></p>

<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=silofy.hackthebox">The Hackthebox VSCode Theme</a> - Decent colors with vibrant code highlighting</p>

<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=eamodio.gitlens">GitLens</a> - Great Git plugin that allows for easier git integration</p>

<p><img src="/images/compsci-images/vscode-git-lens.png" alt="" /></p>

<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=esbenp.prettier-vscode">Prettier</a> - Nice code formatter that works with most langauges</p>

<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=MS-vsliveshare.vsliveshare">Live Share</a> - Microsoft extension that allows you to collaboarte in real time on code projects</p>

<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=mtxr.sqltools">SQLTools</a> - Fantastic extension for working with SQL databases</p>

<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ms-vscode-remote.remote-ssh">Remote - SSH</a> - Allows you to work on remote code hosted on a SSH server</p>

<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ritwickdey.LiveServer">Live Server</a> - Extension that allows you to preview webpages in real time</p>

<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=adpyke.codesnap">Code Snap</a> - One of my favorite extensions by far as it allows you to take really nice looking screenshots of your code</p>

<p><img src="/images/compsci-images/vscode-snap.png" alt="" /></p>

